      <h3>An emerging need for senior support infrastructure</h3>
      <p>
        Through investigating reports released by the National Insititue of
        Aging, my team and myself discovered that 40% of Canadians aged 55+
        reported experiencing a lack of companionship and regular social
        connections with other people, while 67% of Canadians reported believing
        that a lack of social connection negatively impact their overall health
        and wellbeing.
      </p>
      <p>
        A comparative analysis on postal services in other parts of the world
        was conducted by myself and my team. We discovered that offices such as
        La Poste in France and Japan Post are already existing utlizing their
        infrastructure of door-to-door delivery to provide care to seniors who
        are separated from their families via periodical check-ins.
      </p>
      <p>
        With over 26,500 letter carriers employed by Canada Post, my team and I
        believe that there is a reasonable space for the business to intervene
        with the senior care space.
