    <p>
      During user testing and in-class presentations, proposals for Carriers
      that Care were met with concerns around putting postal workers in a
      position where they would have authority in areas that they would not be
      adequately trained for, one example of such including medical care. By
      employing this framework, and committing our focus to the area of social
      connections, my team and myself wanted to ensure that we properly
      establish that we are designing around a domain within senior support that
      postal workers can reasonably intervene with - without reducing
      credibility or trust in Carriers that Care.
    </p>
